'''Daud "Cino" Yordan''' (born 10 June 1987) is an Indonesian professional [[boxing|boxer]] and the former [[International Boxing Organization|IBO]] [[Featherweight]] and [[Lightweight]] Champion. He is now the [[World Boxing Organization|WBO]] Asia-Pacific and Africa [[Lightweight]] Champion. He is ranked 10th in the Lightweight division according to [[BoxRec]]. His main aim right now is to win the [[World Boxing Organization|WBO]] Lightweight Title.

==Early life and family==
Daud was born in [[Ketapang]], [[West Borneo]], [[Indonesia]] on 10 June 1987. He is the fifth child of six children to Hermanus Lai Cun, a [[Chinese Indonesian|Chinese]] father and Natalia, a [[Dayak people|Dayak]] mother.

His former trainer, Carlos Jesus Penate Torres from [[Cuba]] give his nickname ''Cino'' (''Chino'' in Spanish). Since then he is always known by the nickname.<ref>{{cite news|title=Daud ‘Cino’ Jordan|url=http://berlari.blogspot.com/2007/06/daud-cino-jordan.html|newspaper=Borneo Tribune|date=29 June 2007|author=Johan Wahyudi|language=Indonesian}}</ref>

==Professional career==
Yordan fought for the [[World Boxing Association|WBA]] featherweight title against [[Chris John (boxer)|Chris John]] on 17 April 2011 held at the Jakarta International Expo, Kemayoran, Central Jakarta where he lost by unanimous decision.<ref>{{cite news|newspaper=The Jakarta Post|title=Chris John beats Daud Yordan to retain title|url=http://www.thejakartapost.com/news/2011/04/18/chris-john-beats-daud-yordan-retain-title.html|date=18 April 2011|deadurl=yes|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20110521044429/http://www.thejakartapost.com/news/2011/04/18/chris-john-beats-daud-yordan-retain-title.html|archivedate=21 May 2011|df=}}</ref>

Yordan won the vacant [[International Boxing Organization]] [[featherweight]] title by defeating [[Lorenzo Villanueva]] at [[Marina Bay Sands]], [[Singapore]] on 5 May 2012.

