{{use dmy dates|date=August 2013}} This is a '''list of [[Ethiopia]]ns''', sorted by the field for which they are best known. The list includes people born in and residing in Ethiopia, as well as people strongly associated with Ethiopia, and people of significant Ethiopian ancestry. {{TOC right|date=August 2013}}
==Academics and philosophers== {{div col|colwidth=30em}} * [[Alemayehu Fentaw Weldemariam]] * [[Mohamed Hikam Sheikh Abdirahman]], Islamic scholar * [[Amsalu Aklilu]], lexicographer of [[Amharic]] * [[Hizkias Assefa]], professor of conflict studies and consulting mediator * [[Bahrey]], 16th-century monk historian * [[Gäbre-Heywät Baykädañ]] (1886-1919), intellectual and reformer who served as treasurer for Emperor [[Menelik II]] * [[Yosef Ben-Jochannan]], writer and historian * [[Eleni Gebre-Medhin]], economist<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.ethiomedia.com/adroit/2696.html |title=The dangerous hype behind the Ethiopian commodity exchange (or commodity invasion?) |publisher=Ethiomedia.com |date= |accessdate=3 August 2013}}</ref> * [[Gebisa Ejeta]], 2009 World Food Prize laureate and Distinguished Professor at [[Purdue University]] * [[Getatchew Haile]], scholar of the [[Ge'ez language]] * [[Walda Heywat]], philosopher * [[Ephraim Isaac]], scholar of ancient languages * [[Taddesse Tamrat]], Ethiopian historian * [[Sheikh Muhammad Rashid Bilal]] * [[Shekh Muhammad Tānī]], scholar * [[Merid Wolde Aregay]], Ethiopian historian * [[Dawit Mulugeta]], researcher * [[Mesfin Woldemariam]], academician * [[Zera Yacob]], philosopher * [[Zewde Gebre-Sellassie]] {{div col end}}
